WHAT WE LEARNED (DON'T REPEAT)
================================

- Don't write asm after the equation. If you're reaching for
  asm, you haven't found the right coordinates yet.

- DON'T WRITE A SYSTEM.ASM. The x86 files are fixed (boot,
  cpu, handoff, equation, walker, genesis). One agent wrote an
  asm heartbeat. 1389 lines of system.asm existed because the
  foundation was wrong.

- DON'T WRITE AN ASM DRAIN LOOP. It's the bind bond (0,1,1,1).

- DON'T PUT PCI SCAN IN THE BOOTLOADER. Hardware addresses are
  non-local. Port reads, not scans.

- DON'T HARDCODE VESA MODE NUMBERS. Enumerate. Check BPP=32.
  Don't use Bochs VBE ports — QEMU only.

- DON'T ADD SOFTWARE TO GENESIS. Genesis inits hardware and
  fills loops. WM, games, editors are walk data in loops.

- DON'T BLOAT GENESIS. New walk → new file in walks/.
  Genesis is ONE-TIME BOOT. It inits hardware and fills loops.
  WM, games, editors are walk data in loops, not genesis code.

- DON'T CREATE HUMAN ABSTRACTIONS. If it's coordinates, it's
  a walk. Infrastructure around wrong coordinates is the problem.

- EVERYTHING IS MATH. Waves, not bitmaps. Compute, not blit.
  Decompose: read, test, compute, write. Those are bonds.

- CHARACTERS ARE WAVES. Wave bytes in 4D space. Classification
  = dimension check. Rendering = SDF evaluation. Search =
  coordinate comparison. 64 chars per ZMM. One encoding for all.

- THE WAVE BYTE IS THE RECORD. Not compression. The 32-byte
  format was scaffolding. A walk is a byte array.

- THE EQUATION STAYS SEALED. No templates. No new bond types
  for rendering, scrolling, blitting. Decompose to math.


- COMMENT LIKE A RETARD IS READING. Nobody has coded lattice
  walks before. There is no Stack Overflow for this. There is no
  textbook. Every wit that reads this code is seeing it for the
  first time. Every coordinate, every flags byte, every skip
  offset — explain what it does and WHY. "port_write" is not
  enough. Say what port, what value, what happens when you write
  it. The hex is obvious to the wit that wrote it and gibberish
  to the next one. Write for the next one.

- USE walk.inc. Write coordinates, not hex wave bytes.
  w -1,0,0,+1 is a port_write. 0xC1 is a mystery.
  F(U8,U8,P) is two byte args. 0x05 is noise.
  The macros emit identical bytes at zero cost. Use them.


The lattice doesn't add performance and security.
It's what you get when you stop adding everything else.
